The paper discusses a decentralized asset transfer system without the use of consensus, which falls under the category of distributed systems. The paper also discusses algorithms for shared-memory and message passing models, which are subcategories of distributed systems. The paper also discusses fault tolerance and security, which fall under the categories of cryptography and security. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), and cs.Distributed Systems.
